  <Name>k__BackingField: Hosea
  fancyName: 
  nickname: hos
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: "Hosea\u2019s Wife and Children"
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Hosea son
        of Beeri during the years when Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah were kings
        of Judah, and Jeroboam son of Jehoash[[COMMENT(0)]] was king of Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Joash, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoash.
    - title: 
      content: "When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> first began speaking to Israel
        through Hosea, he said to him, \u201CGo and marry a prostitute,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        so that some of her children will be conceived in prostitution. This will
        illustrate how Israel has acted like a prostitute by turning against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and worshiping other gods.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        content: 'Or <b>a promiscuous woman.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: 'So Hosea married Gomer, the daughter of Diblaim, and she became pregnant
        and gave Hosea a son. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CName the child Jezreel,
        for I am about to punish King Jehu\u2019s dynasty to avenge the murders he
        committed at Jezreel. In fact, I will bring an end to Israel\u2019s independence. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will break its military power in the Jezreel Valley.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Soon Gomer became pregnant again and gave birth to a daughter. And
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Hosea, \u201CName your daughter Lo-ruhamah\u2014\u2018Not
        loved\u2019\u2014for I will no longer show love to the people of Israel or
        forgive them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I will show love to the people of Judah. I will free them from
        their enemies\u2014not with weapons and armies or horses and charioteers,
        but by my power as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After Gomer had weaned Lo-ruhamah, she again became pregnant and
        gave birth to a second son. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CName him Lo-ammi\u2014\u2018Not
        my people\u2019\u2014for Israel is not my people, and I am not their God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CYet the time will come when Israel\u2019s people
        will be like the sands of the seashore\u2014too many to count! Then, at the
        place where they were told, \u2018You are not my people,\u2019 it will be
        said, \u2018You are children of the living God.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: '  Verses 1:10-11 are numbered 2:1-2 in Hebrew text.  '
  - verses:
    - title: Charges against an Unfaithful Wife
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CIn that day you will call your brothers Ammi\u2014\u2018My
        people.\u2019 And you will call your sisters Ruhamah\u2014\u2018The ones
        I love.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: '  Verses 2:1-23 are numbered 2:3-25 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut now bring charges against Israel\u2014your mother\u2014for
        she is no longer my wife,and I am no longer her husband.Tell her to remove
        the prostitute\u2019s makeup from her faceand the clothing that exposes her
        breasts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Otherwise, I will strip her as nakedas she was on the day she was
        born.I will leave her to die of thirst,as in a dry and barren wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I will not love her children,for they were conceived in prostitution.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their mother is a shameless prostituteand became pregnant in a shameful
        way.She said, \u2018I\u2019ll run after other loversand sell myself to them
        for food and water,for clothing of wool and linen,and for olive oil and drinks.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor this reason I will fence her in with thornbushes.I will
        block her path with a wallto make her lose her way.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When she runs after her lovers,she won\u2019t be able to catch them.She
        will search for thembut not find them.Then she will think,\u2018I might as
        well return to my husband,for I was better off with him than I am now.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She doesn\u2019t realize it was I who gave her everything she has\u2014the
        grain, the new wine, the olive oil;I even gave her silver and gold.But she
        gave all my gifts to Baal.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut now I will take back the ripened grain and new wineI generously
        provided each harvest season.I will take away the wool and linen clothingI
        gave her to cover her nakedness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will strip her naked in public,while all her lovers look on.No
        one will be ableto rescue her from my hands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will put an end to her annual festivals,her new moon celebrations,
        and her Sabbath days\u2014all her appointed festivals.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will destroy her grapevines and fig trees,things she claims her
        lovers gave her.I will let them grow into tangled thickets,where only wild
        animals will eat the fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Love for Unfaithful Israel"
      content: "I will punish her for all those timeswhen she burned incense to her
        images of Baal,when she put on her earrings and jewelsand went out to look
        for her loversbut forgot all about me,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut then I will win her back once again.I will lead her into
        the desertand speak tenderly to her there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will return her vineyards to herand transform the Valley of Trouble[[COMMENT(0)]]
        into a gateway of hope.She will give herself to me there,as she did long
        ago when she was young,when I freed her from her captivity in Egypt.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>valley of Achor.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "When that day comes,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cyou
        will call me \u2018my husband\u2019instead of \u2018my master.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>\u2018my baal.\u2019</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'O Israel, I will wipe the many names of Baal from your lips,and you
        will never mention them again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day I will make a covenantwith all the wild animals and the
        birds of the skyand the animals that scurry along the groundso they will
        not harm you.I will remove all weapons of war from the land,all swords and
        bows,so you can live unafraidin peace and safety.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will make you my wife forever,showing you righteousness and justice,unfailing
        love and compassion.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will be faithful to you and make you mine,and you will finally
        know me as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day, I will answer,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CI
        will answer the sky as it pleads for clouds.And the sky will answer the earth
        with rain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the earth will answer the thirsty criesof the grain, the grapevines,
        and the olive trees.And they in turn will answer,\u2018Jezreel\u2019\u2014\u2018God
        plants!\u2019  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Hosea\u2019s Wife Is Redeemed"
      content: "  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CGo and love
        your wife again, even though she[[COMMENT(0)]] commits adultery with another
        lover. This will illustrate that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> still loves
        Israel, even though the people have turned to other gods and love to worship
        them.[[COMMENT(1)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:1a '
        content: Or <b>Go and love a woman who.</b>
      - number: '3:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>love their raisin cakes.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'So I bought her back for fifteen pieces of silver[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        five bushels of barley and a measure of wine.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:2a '
        content: Hebrew <b>15 [shekels] of silver, </b>about 6 ounces or 171 grams
          in weight.
      - number: '3:2b '
        content: As in Greek version, which reads <b>a homer of barley and a wineskin
          full of wine; </b>Hebrew reads <b>a homer </b>[5 bushels or 220 liters]
          <b>of barley and a lethek </b>[2.5 bushels or 110 liters] <b>of barley.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said to her, \u201CYou must live in my house for many days
        and stop your prostitution. During this time, you will not have sexual relations
        with anyone, not even with me.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        content: Or <b>and I will live with you.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'This shows that Israel will go a long time without a king or prince,
        and without sacrifices, sacred pillars, priests,[[COMMENT(0)]] or even idols! '
      comments:
      - number: '3:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>ephod, </b>the vest worn by the priest.
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Case against Israel"
      content: "  Hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, O people of Israel!The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has brought charges against you, saying:\u201CThere
        is no faithfulness, no kindness,no knowledge of God in your land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You make vows and break them;you kill and steal and commit adultery.There
        is violence everywhere\u2014one murder after another.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why your land is in mourning,and everyone is wasting away.Even
        the wild animals, the birds of the sky,and the fish of the sea are disappearing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t point your finger at someone elseand try to pass
        the blame!My complaint, you priests,is with you.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Your people are like those with a complaint against the
          priests.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'So you will stumble in broad daylight,and your false prophets will
        fall with you in the night.And I will destroy Israel, your mother.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My people are being destroyedbecause they don\u2019t know me.Since
        you priests refuse to know me,I refuse to recognize you as my priests.Since
        you have forgotten the laws of your God,I will forget to bless your children.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The more priests there are,the more they sin against me.They have
        exchanged the glory of Godfor the shame of idols.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: As in Syriac version and an ancient Hebrew tradition; Masoretic
          Text reads <b>I will turn their glory into shame.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the people bring their sin offerings, the priests get
        fed.So the priests are glad when the people sin!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018And what the priests do, the people also do.\u2019So now I
        will punish both priests and peoplefor their wicked deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will eat and still be hungry.They will play the prostitute and
        gain nothing from it,for they have deserted the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "to worship other gods.\u201CWine has robbed my peopleof their understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They ask a piece of wood for advice!They think a stick can tell them
        the future!Longing after idolshas made them foolish.They have played the
        prostitute,serving other gods and deserting their God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They offer sacrifices to idols on the mountaintops.They go up into
        the hills to burn incensein the pleasant shade of oaks, poplars, and terebinth
        trees.\u201CThat is why your daughters turn to prostitution,and your daughters-in-law
        commit adultery.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But why should I punish themfor their prostitution and adultery?For
        your men are doing the same thing,sinning with whores and shrine prostitutes.O
        foolish people! You refuse to understand,so you will be destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThough you, Israel, are a prostitute,may Judah not be guilty
        of such things.Do not join the false worship at Gilgal or Beth-aven,[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        do not take oaths there in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s name.  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:15 '
        content: "<b>Beth-aven </b>means \u201Chouse of wickedness\u201D; it is being
          used as another name for Bethel, which means \u201Chouse of God.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: 'Israel is stubborn,like a stubborn heifer.So should the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        feed herlike a lamb in a lush pasture?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Leave Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] alone,because she is married to idolatry.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
    - title: 
      content: 'When the rulers of Israel finish their drinking,off they go to find
        some prostitutes.They love shame more than honor.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:18 '
        content: As in Greek version; the meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
  - verses:
    - title: "The Failure of Israel\u2019s Leaders"
      content: "  \u201CHear this, you priests.Pay attention, you leaders of Israel.Listen,
        you members of the royal family.Judgment has been handed down against you.For
        you have led the people into a snareby worshiping the idols at Mizpah and
        Tabor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have dug a deep pit to trap them at Acacia Grove.[[COMMENT(0)]]But
        I will settle with you for what you have done.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>at Shittim. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew for this sentence
          is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'I know what you are like, O Ephraim.You cannot hide yourself from
        me, O Israel.You have left me as a prostitute leaves her husband;you are
        utterly defiled.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your deeds won\u2019t let you return to your God.You are a prostitute
        through and through,and you do not know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe arrogance of Israel testifies against her;Israel and Ephraim
        will stumble under their load of guilt.Judah, too, will fall with them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they come with their flocks and herdsto offer sacrifices to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,they will not find him,because he has withdrawn
        from them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have betrayed the honor of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,bearing
        children that are not his.Now their false religion will devour themalong
        with their wealth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:7 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSound the alarm in Gibeah!Blow the trumpet in Ramah!Raise the
        battle cry in Beth-aven[[COMMENT(0)]]!Lead on into battle, O warriors of
        Benjamin!  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:8 '
        content: "<b>Beth-aven </b>means \u201Chouse of wickedness\u201D; it is being
          used as another name for Bethel, which means \u201Chouse of God.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: 'One thing is certain, Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]:On your day of punishment,you
        will become a heap of rubble.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel;
          also in 5:11, 12, 13, 14.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe leaders of Judah have become like thieves.[[COMMENT(0)]]So
        I will pour my anger on them like a waterfall.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>like those who move a boundary marker.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The people of Israel will be crushed and broken by my judgmentbecause
        they are determined to worship idols.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:11 '
        content: Or <b>determined to follow human commands. </b>The meaning of the
          Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'I will destroy Israel as a moth consumes wool.I will make Judah as
        weak as rotten wood.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen Israel and Judah saw how sick they were,Israel turned
        to Assyria\u2014to the great king there\u2014but he could neither help nor
        cure them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will be like a lion to Israel,like a strong young lion to Judah.I
        will tear them to pieces!I will carry them off,and no one will be left to
        rescue them.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Repentance
      content: "  \u201CCome, let us return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.He
        has torn us to pieces;now he will heal us.He has injured us;now he will bandage
        our wounds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In just a short time he will restore us,so that we may live in his
        presence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, that we might know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Let us press
        on to know him.He will respond to us as surely as the arrival of dawnor the
        coming of rains in early spring.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] and Judah,what should I do with you?\u201D
        asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CFor your love vanishes like the
        morning mistand disappears like dew in the sunlight.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
    - title: 
      content: "I sent my prophets to cut you to pieces\u2014to slaughter you with
        my words,with judgments as inescapable as light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I want you to show love,[[COMMENT(0)]]not offer sacrifices.I want
        you to know me[[COMMENT(1)]]more than I want burnt offerings.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:6a '
        content: Greek version translates this Hebrew term as <b>to show mercy. </b>Compare
          Matt 9:13; 12:7.
      - number: '6:6b '
        content: Hebrew <b>to know God.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But like Adam,[[COMMENT(0)]] you broke my covenantand betrayed my
        trust.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:7 '
        content: Or <b>But at Adam.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGilead is a city of sinners,tracked with footprints of blood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Priests form bands of robbers,waiting in ambush for their victims.They
        murder travelers along the road to Shechemand practice every kind of sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, I have seen something horrible in Ephraim and Israel:My people
        are defiled by prostituting themselves with other gods!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Love for Wickedness"
      content: "  \u201CI want to heal Israel, but its[[COMMENT(0)]] sins are too
        great.Samaria is filled with liars.Thieves are on the insideand bandits on
        the outside!  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:1 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Ephraim\u2019s, </b>referring to the northern kingdom
          of Israel; similarly in 7:8, 11."
    - title: 
      content: "Its people don\u2019t realizethat I am watching them.Their sinful
        deeds are all around them,and I see them all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe people entertain the king with their wickedness,and the
        princes laugh at their lies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are all adulterers,always aflame with lust.They are like an
        oven that is kept hotwhile the baker is kneading the dough.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On royal holidays, the princes get drunk with wine,carousing with
        those who mock them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their hearts are like an ovenblazing with intrigue.Their plot smolders[[COMMENT(0)]]
        through the night,and in the morning it breaks out like a raging fire.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Their baker sleeps.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Burning like an oven,they consume their leaders.They kill their kings
        one after another,and no one cries to me for help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe people of Israel mingle with godless foreigners,making
        themselves as worthless as a half-baked cake!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Worshiping foreign gods has sapped their strength,but they don\u2019t
        even know it.Their hair is gray,but they don\u2019t realize they\u2019re
        old and weak.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their arrogance testifies against them,yet they don\u2019t return
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their Godor even try to find him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe people of Israel have become like silly, witless doves,first
        calling to Egypt, then flying to Assyria for help.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But as they fly about,I will throw my net over themand bring them
        down like a bird from the sky.I will punish them for all the evil they do.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>I will punish them because of what was reported against
          them in the assembly.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits those who have deserted me!Let them die,
        for they have rebelled against me.I wanted to redeem them,but they have told
        lies about me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They do not cry out to me with sincere hearts.Instead, they sit on
        their couches and wail.They cut themselves,[[COMMENT(0)]] begging foreign
        gods for grain and new wine,and they turn away from me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:14 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>They gather together.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I trained them and made them strong,yet now they plot evil against
        me.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Israel Harvests the Whirlwind
      content: "  \u201CSound the alarm!The enemy descends like an eagle on the people
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for they have broken my covenantand revolted
        against my law.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now Israel pleads with me,\u2018Help us, for you are our God!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But it is too late.The people of Israel have rejected what is good,and
        now their enemies will chase after them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people have appointed kings without my consent,and princes without
        my approval.By making idols for themselves from their silver and gold,they
        have brought about their own destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO Samaria, I reject this calf\u2014this idol you have made.My
        fury burns against you.How long will you be incapable of innocence?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This calf you worship, O Israel,was crafted by your own hands!It
        is not God!Therefore, it must be smashed to bits.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey have planted the windand will harvest the whirlwind.The
        stalks of grain witherand produce nothing to eat.And even if there is any
        grain,foreigners will eat it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people of Israel have been swallowed up;they lie among the nations
        like an old discarded pot.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Like a wild donkey looking for a mate,they have gone up to Assyria.The
        people of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] have sold themselves\u2014sold themselves
        to many lovers.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel;
          also in 8:11.
    - title: 
      content: 'But though they have sold themselves to many allies,I will now gather
        them together for judgment.Then they will writheunder the burden of the great
        king.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIsrael has built many altars to take away sin,but these very
        altars became places for sinning!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even though I gave them all my laws,they act as if those laws don\u2019t
        apply to them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people love to offer sacrifices to me,feasting on the meat,but
        I do not accept their sacrifices.I will hold my people accountable for their
        sins,and I will punish them.They will return to Egypt.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Hosea Announces Israel\u2019s Punishment"
      content: '  O people of Israel,do not rejoice as other nations do.For you have
        been unfaithful to your God,hiring yourselves out like prostitutes,worshiping
        other gods on every threshing floor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So now your harvests will be too small to feed you.There will be
        no grapes for making new wine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You may no longer stay here in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        land.Instead, you will return to Egypt,and in Assyria you will eat foodthat
        is ceremonially unclean.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There you will make no offerings of wine to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.None
        of your sacrifices there will please him.They will be unclean, like food
        touched by a person in mourning.All who present such sacrifices will be defiled.They
        may eat this food themselves,but they may not offer it to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What then will you do on festival days?How will you observe the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        festivals?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if you escape destruction from Assyria,Egypt will conquer you,
        and Memphis[[COMMENT(0)]] will bury you.Nettles will take over your treasures
        of silver;thistles will invade your ruined homes.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:6 '
        content: Memphis was the capital of northern Egypt.
    - title: 
      content: "The time of Israel\u2019s punishment has come;the day of payment
        is here.Soon Israel will know this all too well.Because of your great sin
        and hostility,you say, \u201CThe prophets are crazyand the inspired men are
        fools!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The prophet is a watchman over Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] for my God,yet
        traps are laid for him wherever he goes.He faces hostility even in the house
        of God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel;
          also in 9:11, 13, 16.
    - title: 
      content: 'The things my people do are as depravedas what they did in Gibeah
        long ago.God will not forget.He will surely punish them for their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CO Israel, when I first
        found you,it was like finding fresh grapes in the desert.When I saw your
        ancestors,it was like seeing the first ripe figs of the season.But then they
        deserted me for Baal-peor,giving themselves to that shameful idol.Soon they
        became vile,as vile as the god they worshiped.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The glory of Israel will fly away like a bird,for your children will
        not be bornor grow in the wombor even be conceived.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if you do have children who grow up,I will take them from you.It
        will be a terrible day when I turn awayand leave you alone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have watched Israel become as beautiful as Tyre.But now Israel
        will bring out her children for slaughter.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, what should I request for your people?I
        will ask for wombs that don\u2019t give birthand breasts that give no milk.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CAll their wickedness
        began at Gilgal;there I began to hate them.I will drive them from my landbecause
        of their evil actions.I will love them no morebecause all their leaders are
        rebels.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Israel are struck down.Their roots are dried up,and
        they will bear no more fruit.And if they give birth,I will slaughter their
        beloved children.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Judgment against Israel"
      content: "  How prosperous Israel is\u2014a luxuriant vine loaded with fruit.But
        the richer the people get,the more pagan altars they build.The more bountiful
        their harvests,the more beautiful their sacred pillars.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The hearts of the people are fickle;they are guilty and must be punished.The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will break down their altarsand smash their sacred
        pillars.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they will say, \u201CWe have no kingbecause we didn\u2019t fear
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.But even if we had a king,what could he do
        for us anyway?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They spout empty wordsand make covenants they don\u2019t intend to
        keep.So injustice springs up among themlike poisonous weeds in a farmer\u2019s
        field.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people of Samaria tremble in fearfor their calf idol at Beth-aven,[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        they mourn for it.Though its priests rejoice over it,its glory will be stripped
        away.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:5a '
        content: "<b>Beth-aven </b>means \u201Chouse of wickedness\u201D; it is being
          used as another name for Bethel, which means \u201Chouse of God.\u201D"
      - number: '10:5b '
        content: Or <b>will be taken away into exile.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'This idol will be carted away to Assyria,a gift to the great king
        there.Ephraim will be ridiculed and Israel will be shamed,because its people
        have trusted in this idol.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Samaria and its king will be cut off;they will float away like driftwood
        on an ocean wave.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the pagan shrines of Aven,[[COMMENT(0)]] the place of Israel\u2019s
        sin, will crumble.Thorns and thistles will grow up around their altars.They
        will beg the mountains, \u201CBury us!\u201Dand plead with the hills, \u201CFall
        on us!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:8 '
        content: <b>Aven </b>is a reference to Beth-aven; see 10:5a and the note
          there.
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CO Israel, ever since
        Gibeah,there has been only sin and more sin!You have made no progress whatsoever.Was
        it not right that the wicked men of Gibeah were attacked?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now whenever it fits my plan,I will attack you, too.I will call out
        the armies of the nationsto punish you for your multiplied sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIsrael[[COMMENT(0)]] is like a trained heifer treading out
        the grain\u2014an easy job she loves.But I will put a heavy yoke on her tender
        neck.I will force Judah to pull the plowand Israel[[COMMENT(1)]] to break
        up the hard ground.  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:11a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
      - number: '10:11b '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Jacob. </b>The names \u201CJacob\u201D and \u201CIsrael\u201D
          are often interchanged throughout the Old Testament, referring sometimes
          to the individual patriarch and sometimes to the nation."
    - title: 
      content: "I said, \u2018Plant the good seeds of righteousness,and you will
        harvest a crop of love.Plow up the hard ground of your hearts,for now is
        the time to seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,that he may comeand shower
        righteousness upon you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you have cultivated wickednessand harvested a thriving
        crop of sins.You have eaten the fruit of lies\u2014trusting in your military
        might,believing that great armiescould make your nation safe.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now the terrors of warwill rise among your people.All your fortifications
        will fall,just as when Shalman destroyed Beth-arbel.Even mothers and childrenwere
        dashed to death there.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Love for Israel"
      content: "  \u201CWhen Israel was a child, I loved him,and I called my son
        out of Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the more I called to him,the farther he moved from me,[[COMMENT(0)]]offering
        sacrifices to the images of Baaland burning incense to idols.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:2 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>the more they called to him,
          the farther he moved from them.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "I myself taught Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] how to walk,leading him along
        by the hand.But he doesn\u2019t know or even carethat it was I who took care
        of him.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel;
          also in 11:8, 9, 12.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'I led Israel alongwith my ropes of kindness and love.I lifted the
        yoke from his neck,and I myself stooped to feed him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut since my people refuse to return to me,they will return
        to Egyptand will be forced to serve Assyria.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'War will swirl through their cities;their enemies will crash through
        their gates.They will destroy them,trapping them in their own evil plans.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For my people are determined to desert me.They call me the Most High,but
        they don\u2019t truly honor me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COh, how can I give you up, Israel?How can I let you go?How
        can I destroy you like Admahor demolish you like Zeboiim?My heart is torn
        within me,and my compassion overflows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, I will not unleash my fierce anger.I will not completely destroy
        Israel,for I am God and not a mere mortal.I am the Holy One living among
        you,and I will not come to destroy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For someday the people will follow me.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        will roar like a lion.And when I roar,my people will return trembling from
        the west.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Charges against Israel and Judah
      content: "Like a flock of birds, they will come from Egypt.Trembling like doves,
        they will return from Assyria.And I will bring them home again,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]The people of Israel[[COMMENT(1)]] feed on the
        wind;they chase after the east wind all day long.They pile up lies and violence;they
        are making an alliance with Assyriawhile sending olive oil to buy support
        from Egypt.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:1a '
        content: '  Verses 12:1-14 are numbered 12:2-15 in Hebrew text.  '
      - number: '12:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel;
          also in 12:8, 14.
    - title: 
      content: 'Now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is bringing charges against Judah.He
        is about to punish Jacob[[COMMENT(0)]] for all his deceitful ways,and pay
        him back for all he has done.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:2 '
        content: "<b>Jacob </b>sounds like the Hebrew word for \u201Cdeceiver.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: 'Even in the womb,Jacob struggled with his brother;when he became
        a man,he even fought with God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, he wrestled with the angel and won.He wept and pleaded for a
        blessing from him.There at Bethel he met God face to face,and God spoke to
        him[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:4 '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads <b>to us.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s Armies,the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is his name!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So now, come back to your God.Act with love and justice,and always
        depend on him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But no, the people are like crafty merchantsselling from dishonest
        scales\u2014they love to cheat.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Israel boasts, \u201CI am rich!I\u2019ve made a fortune all by myself!No
        one has caught me cheating!My record is spotless!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,who rescued
        you from slavery in Egypt.And I will make you live in tents again,as you
        do each year at the Festival of Shelters.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>as in the days of your appointed feast.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "I sent my prophets to warn youwith many visions and parables.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the people of Gilead are worthlessbecause of their idol worship.And
        in Gilgal, too, they sacrifice bulls;their altars are lined up like the heaps
        of stonealong the edges of a plowed field.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jacob fled to the land of Aram,and there he[[COMMENT(0)]] earned
        a wife by tending sheep.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Israel. </b>See note on 10:11b.
    - title: 
      content: "Then by a prophetthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> brought Jacob\u2019s
        descendants[[COMMENT(0)]] out of Egypt;and by that prophetthey were protected.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>brought Israel. </b>See note on 10:11b.
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Anger against Israel"
      content: '  When the tribe of Ephraim spoke,the people shook with fear,for
        that tribe was important in Israel.But the people of Ephraim sinned by worshiping
        Baaland thus sealed their destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now they continue to sin by making silver idols,images shaped skillfully
        with human hands.\u201CSacrifice to these,\u201D they cry,\u201Cand kiss
        the calf idols!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, they will disappear like the morning mist,like dew in
        the morning sun,like chaff blown by the wind,like smoke from a chimney.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have been the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your Godever since
        I brought you out of Egypt.You must acknowledge no God but me,for there is
        no other savior.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I took care of you in the wilderness,in that dry and thirsty land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when you had eaten and were satisfied,you became proud and forgot
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So now I will attack you like a lion,like a leopard that lurks along
        the road.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Like a bear whose cubs have been taken away,I will tear out your
        heart.I will devour you like a hungry lionessand mangle you like a wild animal.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou are about to be destroyed, O Israel\u2014yes, by me, your
        only helper.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now where is[[COMMENT(0)]] your king?Let him save you!Where are all
        the leaders of the land,the king and the officials you demanded of me?  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:10 '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions and Latin Vulgate; Hebrew reads
          <b>I will be.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'In my anger I gave you kings,and in my fury I took them away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEphraim\u2019s guilt has been collected,and his sin has been
        stored up for punishment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pain has come to the peoplelike the pain of childbirth,but they are
        like a childwho resists being born.The moment of birth has arrived,but they
        stay in the womb!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CShould I ransom them from the grave[[COMMENT(0)]]?Should I
        redeem them from death?O death, bring on your terrors!O grave, bring on your
        plagues![[COMMENT(1)]]For I will not take pity on them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:14a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol; </b>also in 13:14b.
      - number: '13:14b '
        content: 'Greek version reads <b>O death, where is your punishment? / O grave
          </b>[Hades], <b>where is your sting? </b>Compare 1 Cor 15:55.  '
    - title: 
      content: "Ephraim was the most fruitful of all his brothers,but the east wind\u2014a
        blast from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014will arise in the desert.All
        their flowing springs will run dry,and all their wells will disappear.Every
        precious thing they ownwill be plundered and carried away.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Healing for the Repentant
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]Return, O Israel, to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God,for your sins have brought you down.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:1 '
        content: '  Verses 14:1-9 are numbered 14:2-10 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: "Bring your confessions, and return to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Say
        to him,\u201CForgive all our sins and graciously receive us,so that we may
        offer you our praises.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:2 '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions, which read <b>may repay the fruit
          of our lips; </b>Hebrew reads <b>may repay the bulls of our lips.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Assyria cannot save us,nor can our warhorses.Never again will we
        say to the idols we have made,\u2018You are our gods.\u2019No, in you alonedo
        the orphans find mercy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,\u201CThen I will heal you of
        your faithlessness;my love will know no bounds,for my anger will be gone
        forever.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will be to Israellike a refreshing dew from heaven.Israel will
        blossom like the lily;it will send roots deep into the soillike the cedars
        in Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its branches will spread out like beautiful olive trees,as fragrant
        as the cedars of Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My people will again live under my shade.They will flourish like
        grain and blossom like grapevines.They will be as fragrant as the wines of
        Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]] stay away from idols!I am the one who
        answers your prayers and cares for you.I am like a tree that is always green;all
        your fruit comes from me.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
